description.text:
&lt;p&gt;This lecture is organized as part of Hyderabad Workshop on Information Theory (HyWIT) 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This talk will focus on Sparse Bayesian Learning (SBL) approach to compressive sensing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will specifically consider the application of direction-of-arrival (DOA) estimation from&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sensor array measurements.&amp;nbsp;Results from&amp;nbsp;simulation and experimental data&amp;nbsp;demonstrate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the super-resolution ability of SBL&amp;nbsp;compared to traditional method such as MUSIC.&amp;nbsp;We&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;also look at sparse arrays such as co-prime and nested arrays and their difference co-array.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike uniform arrays, sparse arrays can identify more sources than the number of sensors&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;as will be seen from simulation and data results&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot; title=&quot;Page 1&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In thistalk, we will first consider the challenges of developing a communication system for drone-to-ground links. As a first step, experiments to model the wireless channels for such links are being carried out in IISc. The channel measurement system design and data collection methodology will be presented. Based on the data collection, preliminary channel models based on these measurements will be presented in the talk using signal processing concepts like convolution, correlation.&lt;/p&gt;
